  "publisher": "dc",
  "about": "\"DC One Million\" is a comic book crossover storyline which ran through an eponymous weekly miniseries and through special issues of almost all of the \"DCU\" titles published by DC Comics in November 1998. It featured a vision of the DC Universe in the 853rd century (85,201–85,300 AD), chosen because that is the century in which DC will have published issue #1,000,000 of Action Comics if it maintains a regular monthly publishing schedule. The miniseries was written by Grant Morrison and drawn by Val Semeiks.",
  "note": null,
